SIMPLE: onward
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Onward
<hw>On"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving in
a forward direction; tending toward a contemplated or desirable end;
forward; <as>as, an <ex>onward</ex> course, progress,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Advanced in a forward direction or toward an
end.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Within a while, Philoxenus came to see how <qex>onward</qex> the
fruits were of his friend's labor.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P.
Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onward</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Onward
<hw>On"ward</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Toward a point before or in
front; forward; progressively; <as>as, to move
<ex>onward</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not one looks backward, <qex>onward</qex> still he goes.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onwardness</ent>⟦br⟧
